data.name: FetchResult
desc: contains data of several rows of a ContentResultSet.
This struct is returned from XFetchProvider.fetch(), for example.

items.name: FetchError
lines: indicates whether and which error has occurred, while fetching.
The value may contain zero or more constants of the FetchError constants group.

items.name: Orientation
lines: indicates the orientation in which the rows are fetched and set into the sequence FetchResult.Rows.
When FetchResult.Orientation equals TRUE, the rows in FetchResult.Rows are ordered in the same way as in the original result set.

items.name: StartIndex
lines: indicates the index of the first row contained in FetchResult.Rows in the original result set.
So if FetchResult.StartIndex equals 3, the first element in the sequence FetchResult.Rows contains the data of the index 3 in the original result set.
The following rows are one after the other, but the direction depends on the value of FetchResult.Direction

items.name: Rows
lines: One any contains the data of one whole row. Those methods which use this struct have to specify, what the any has to contain.
